-- Allstate profit falls 17 percent
-- 
-- Tue May 06, 2014 04:13PM EDT
-- None



May 6 (Reuters) - Insurer Allstate Corp <ALL.N> posted a 17 percent fall in quarterly profit as losses from disasters soared due to a more severe winter than usual across most of North America.

The company's net income available to common shareholders fell to $587 million, or $1.30 per share, in the quarter ended March 31, from $709 million, or $1.47 per share, a year earlier.